  <section class="local-section" id="local">
    <h2>Chimney Sweeping in Mornington</h2>
    <div class="local-box"><p>Mornington is the commercial and residential hub of the upper Mornington Peninsula, a town with genuine heritage dating to the 1850s that has grown steadily through every era of Melbourne's suburban expansion. The housing stock in Mornington is unusually diverse: the older residential streets behind Main Street contain Victorian and Edwardian weatherboards and brick homes, the interwar and postwar eras contributed brick bungalows and fibro cottages, and the peninsula's enduring popularity as a holiday and sea-change destination has added a large stock of weekender beach houses across every decade from the 1940s to the present. This mix of housing ages and uses creates a distinctive chimney servicing pattern: permanent residents who use their fireplaces every winter through the peninsula's cold and often foggy season, and weekender and holiday home owners whose fireplaces may only be lit for a few weeks or a long weekend a year. A fireplace that is used occasionally after sitting dormant for months — often with accumulated debris, nesting activity and dried creosote from the previous season — carries a higher fire risk than one in continuous use. The Mornington Peninsula's winter climate is cold and often damp, with Bass Strait southerlies pushing cold air up the bay and creating genuine heating needs that make a properly maintained fireplace valuable. We service Mornington and the surrounding peninsula suburbs regularly.</p></div>
  </section>

